g to merge it.<br /><br />We do not do "flag-day" things. We've done them in the past, and it<br />has always been a major and unacceptable pain.<br /><br />And if the dependency ordering is "outside" of the traditional<br />link-time ordering, then it is by definition a flag-day event. Every<br />time you add a dependency to even just *one* driver, it magically<br />changes ordering wrt all the other drivers, because now it's in a<br />different ordering domain.<br /><br />So please reconsider. Or stop cc'ing me. Because "flag day" changes<br />really are not acceptable.<br /><br />                       Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
